{"title":"ENVE tests new one-piece SES Aero Road Bar/Stem","link":"https://bikerumor.com/enve-tests-new-one-piece-ses-aero-road-bar-stem/","date":1688921932000,"content":"<p>UAE Emirates rider Tadej Pogacar is riding a new one-piece ENVE SES Aero Road cockpit, combining the handlebar and stem into a single part.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Utah-based brand worked with the team and riders to develop the stiffness, weight, and aerodynamics specifically to Pogacar’s wishes, starting the project in January and delivering a finished product for the entire team to use in under four months. And now they’re racing it at the Tour de France.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-a.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-a.jpg\" alt=\"ENVE one-piece SES aero handlebar-stem cockpit for Tadej Pogacar in tour de france 2023\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-a.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-a-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-a-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-a-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-a-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-a-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-a-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Photos: <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/fizzaazzif\" target=\"_blank\">Lorenzo Fizza Verdinelli</a> and ENVE.</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s based on their current <a href=\"https://www.enve.com/product/aero-handlebar/\" target=\"_blank\">SES Aero Road Handlebar</a>, but with a few geometry tweaks Pogacar requested. It also uses the fully internal IN-Route wire and hose routing, but with a twist.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-b.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2030\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-b.jpg\" alt=\"ENVE one-piece SES aero handlebar-stem cockpit for Tadej Pogacar in tour de france 2023\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-b.jpg 2030w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-b-297x195.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-b-800x525.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-b-120x79.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-b-768x504.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-b-1536x1009.jpg 1536w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The original IN-Route parts pair separate bar and stem, running all control lines through each, then into a <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/chris-king-aeroset-brings-full-internal-cable-integration-to-classic-headsets/\" target=\"_blank\">Chris King Aeroset 3</a> headset. For these, they’re working on making additional spacers and routing options that’ll work with a wider range of headsets and frames, including the Specialized Tarmac. And, we’re guessing from the looks of things, Colnagos, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All of those accessories should be available when this new one-piece bar/stem goes on sale later this year.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-d.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1400\" height=\"2101\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-d.jpg\" alt=\"Tadej Pogacar riding prototype ENVE one-piece SES aero handlebar-stem cockpit in tour de france 2023\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-d.jpg 1400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-d-200x300.jpg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-d-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-d-80x120.jpg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-d-768x1153.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-d-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/one-piece-enve-handlebar-stem-pogacar-tour-de-france-2023-d-1365x2048.jpg 1365w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While official pricing and specs are TBA, ENVE says that they’ve made them in 5mm stem length increments for the team (Tadej is on a 125mm, FYI) and hope to do the same in production, giving all of us the ability to fine tune fit even better than with traditional 10mm-increment stem lengths. They say the weight is around 340g.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.enve.com\" target=\"_blank\">ENVE.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/enve-tests-new-one-piece-ses-aero-road-bar-stem/\">ENVE tests new one-piece SES Aero Road Bar/Stem</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"5a4088a09481e9edc7eab789ee019a3cd3c25d10886acb38969dbcf3f497c7d7","category":"Cycling"}